Hello all,

I'm a beginner with all of this, but I'm trying to set up a plug flow 
for methane oxidation.  I've downloaded several methane oxidation 
mechanisms (mill-bowman, leeds university, etc.), but I'm having 
trouble figuring out how to convert them to cti format.  

The files get downloaded in htm format, which I then re-save as .inp; 
when I run ck2cti (for example, typing "ck2cti -i metan15_dat.htm" in 
matlab) I get an error message.  The ck2cti.log file tells me "no 
elements found."  

Any ideas?

Thanks,
Steven
